whata
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:2
Definition:in esp. SI English, and in esp. early station contexts (?mainly but not exclusively Canterbury and Otago) a storehouse (often roofed) raised off the ground, usu. on poles (?as used by early explorers for provsion caches, often temporarily made) ; `a (rat-proof) storehouse on pole(s)',
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:futtah
Pronunciation:-
