Quote:  Another small structure with walls and a roof thatched with tree fern and called a `whata' was used [c1850s] as a store-room on the station, this was erected on four strong piles rising six feet out of the ground and encircled with tin near the upper part to keep off the rats, these vermin sometimes proving very destructive on account of their large numbers.
